        <section>
        <h2>Cycle of improvement</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Fit many stellar spectra ($N > 50$)</li>    
        <li>Learn the covariance structure including bad regions</li>    
        <li>Use the covariance matrix to regress out what the model <em>should</em> be. <small>This is not unlike how the $UBVRI$ photometric passbands are determined (Bessell &amp; Simon 2012).</small></li>    
        </ol>
        <div class="fragment">
        <p>These improvements to the models could be used to inform the modellers what might need improvement.</p>
        <p>If you're impatient/a DIY-er, you can use your own self-calibrated synthetic spectra.</p>
        </div>
